                {
                  "system": "http://loinc.org",
                  "code": "67781-5",
                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, thank you for referring this 61-year-old male patient admitted on 10/02/2019 due to substance dependence disorder. On admission, a comprehensive psychiatric and somatic assessment was performed, confirming polysubstance dependence. Withdrawal symptoms were monitored and managed accordingly. During the inpatient stay, the patient underwent structured detoxification, supportive pharmacotherapy to manage withdrawal, and motivational counselling sessions. Laboratory investigations and vital sign monitoring were conducted throughout. The patient was stabilised successfully without complications. At discharge on 12/02/2019, the patient was in a clinically stable condition. We strongly recommend follow-up with addiction medicine outpatient services and continuation of psychosocial support. Please find enclosed our discharge summary and medication plan. We remain available for any queries.</div>"
            },
